This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) and their optimization for dynamic inference. Additionally, the use of reinforcement learning for neural architecture search suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves optimization techniques for reducing computational cost, which could fall under the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
